<DIV>&nbsp; I don't play a bard though I love grouping with them and aggro kiting, fear kiting....shame much grouping fun when the mobs are moving is gone. I've admired many bards solo kite mobs, it doesn't look easy, takes them a LONG time. Never been trained by most of these honest, quiet soloer bards, they watch and know where they are and know to stay away from others in the zone.Many times I see their corpses too when they snag up a caster or a named.&nbsp; I also use dial-up and I'm not lagged watching or grouping with kiting bards.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;I wish there was a better way to deal with this problem (what ever the whole problem is) rather then reducing gameplay for some...no matter how small that population of good honest bards-FUN are effected by this nurf. This change may seem small to some or most...but all the 'small' gameplay changes to various classes add up over time.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks again for the great commune Grumbuk, you're the best!</DIV>
																		
