			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>So, let's see.&nbsp; I don't have a 65 level bard or even close.&nbsp;&nbsp; I have only AE kited 6 times (kobolds or minotaurs(2 BTW)&nbsp;in Akanon)&nbsp; to see what it was about.&nbsp;&nbsp;Died twice&nbsp;and decided to play other ways (group/solo -&gt; melee/songs).&nbsp; So, my melee is around 50% of a warrior's from what I can tell, I have no dmg mitigation, my fizzle rate at level 28 on level 5-7 songs (selos/warsong) is absolutely amazingly high even though my song skills are maxed for my level.&nbsp;&nbsp; My only DD spell does 13 pts/6 seconds (laughable for a level&nbsp;5 wizard/shaman/mage/druid).&nbsp;&nbsp; Now I have to rely on the INTENT of the mob as to whether they want to move for a song I am playing while fighting them to do damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; OK, given the little developer effort available to fix a completely broken AE bard kiting situation by what seems to be a small % of the bards -&gt; which is a small % of the characters (sarcasm here), then this is acceptible for the current time mostly given the server occupancy issues.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It is a reasonable compromise for now.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Can I also get a quick fix scheduled for the 50+ level characters pulling whole floors and monopolizing camps to PL their friends and alts?&nbsp;&nbsp; I see that about 10 to 20+ times more than an AE kiting bard.&nbsp;&nbsp; Maybe having a max level range for zones where your character only acts as the max level of the zone.&nbsp; Thus, on entering Unrest with a 56 level paladin you only act as a 35 level paladin as far as hp, spells, melee, etc.&nbsp; How about more level restrictions on gear so I don't see a single 19 level monk with a procing staff + uber gear camping an entire PC bandit camp?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I have a lot of characters to play and so will just semi-retire the bard or play it in the right group situation.&nbsp; As they say,</DIV>
